<TITLE> Justice Khairul made new JSC chief </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 24 (bdnews24.com)  Appellate Division judge ABM Khairul Haque was appointed the new chairman of the Judicial Services Commission on Wednesday. As the commission chair, he is responsible for employment, transfers and promotions within the judicial department. The position has been vacant since Dec 23 when Justice Md Tafazzal Islam, now retired, was appointed as the chief justice. Justice Khairul Haque was appointed as a judge of the Appellate Division on July 16, 2009. He started working as a temporary judge of the High Court Division in 1998 and was made permanent in 2000. Khairul Haque was born in Madaripur on May 18, 1944. He will go into retirement on May 17, 2011. bdnews
